<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFB06739FF4E0B90594C575B" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E0B90594C575B" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0B905968569C" bold="true" box="[185,312,166,192]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0B905963569C" box="[185,307,166,192]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Can be easily recognized by its long embolus, starting at position about 5 h and making 1.5 coils (Figs 4.1, 5.1, 6.1); and by the shape of tegular apophysis and epigyne.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFB06739FF4E0A26595A5712" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E0A26595A5712" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0A2659005776" bold="true" box="[185,336,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0A26591B5776" box="[185,331,272,298]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Redescribed in detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FD8C0A275B585776" author="Levy G" box="[635,776,272,299]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref19351" refString="Levy G (2003) Spiders of the families Anyphaenidae, Hahniidae, Ctenidae, Zoridae, and Hersiliidae (Araneae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 49: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2003">Levy (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and Rheims et al. (2004, as 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FF7B0A0258A95711" box="[140,249,308,333]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF7B0A0258A95711" box="[140,249,308,333]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFB06739FF4E0A605A2554F2" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E0A605C735434" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0A60596F572C" bold="true" box="[185,319,342,368]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E0A60596A572C" box="[185,314,342,368]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FD6E0A615A88572D" box="[665,728,343,369]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and later reported from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FC170A615C7E572D" box="[992,1070,343,369]" name="Algeria" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FBCF0A6158E257C8" name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FF110A4C592657C8" box="[230,374,378,404]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
. Its 
<typeStatus id="0E08AEFEFFB06739FE690A4C598557C8" box="[414,469,378,404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">types</typeStatus>
appear to be lost (
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FD620A4C5B5C57C8" author="Levy G" box="[661,780,378,404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref19351" refString="Levy G (2003) Spiders of the families Anyphaenidae, Hahniidae, Ctenidae, Zoridae, and Hersiliidae (Araneae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 49: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2003">Levy 2003</bibRefCitation>
). It is very likely that that specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FEE40AAB59F357E4" box="[275,419,413,440]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
(males) illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FD6F0AAB5C0457E4" author="Foord SH &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman AS" box="[664,1108,413,440]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="255 - 279" refId="ref18755" refString="Foord SH, Dippenaar-Schoeman AS (2005) A revision of the Afrotropical species of Hersiliola Thorell and Tama Simon with the description of a new genus Tyrotama (Araneae: Hersiliidae). African Entomology 13 (2): 255 - 279." type="journal article" year="2005">Foord and Dippenaar-Schoeman (2005)</bibRefCitation>
are not conspecific with specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FDB10AF65AC15786" box="[582,657,448,474]" name="Algeria" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(females). Males from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FC7B0AF65C4B5787" box="[908,1051,448,475]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
have their embolus base in another position (at 04 hrs) compared to specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FC2E0AD55C4657A1" box="[985,1046,483,509]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Spain</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FBCF0AD258E2547D" name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Israel</collectingCountry>
(at 05 hrs). African males may belong to 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FD9E09315BCE547D" authority="Blackwall, 1865" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1865" box="[617,926,518,545]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FD9E09315AB9547D" box="[617,745,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. versicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FD1809315BCE547D" author="Blackwall J" box="[751,926,518,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref18041" refString="Blackwall J (1865) Descriptions of recently discovered spiders collected in the Cape de Verde Islands by John Gray, Esq. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (3) 16: 80 - 101." type="journal article" year="1865">Blackwall, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FF3C091C591A5418" box="[203,330,554,580]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
from females only. Another possibility is that specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="A9A450CCFFB06739FC0B091C58EC5434" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
had a partially expanded bulbus, and its tegulum was slightly displaced (turned).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E09465A2554F2" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
Figures of “ 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FEC909475B7D54D6" authority="&quot; in Rheims and Brescovit (2004)" authorityName="&quot; in Rheims and Brescovit" authorityYear="2004" box="[318,813,624,650]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FEC9094759FC54D6" box="[318,428,625,650]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. simoni</emphasis>
” in Rheims and Brescovit (2004)
</taxonomicName>
and Rheims et al. (2004) undoubtedly correspond to 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FE3F09A25A3E54F1" baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[456,622,659,685]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FE3F09A25A3E54F1" box="[456,622,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A943D7FFB06739FF4E09805BA852E2" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E09805B3F55DE" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E09805908548C" bold="true" box="[185,344,694,720]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E09805903548C" box="[185,339,694,720]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FE9609815A58548D" baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[353,520,695,721]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FE9609815A58548D" box="[353,520,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed here from 
