<paragraph id="D10C105CFFB06739FF4E08BC5BA852E2" blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E08BC58A955F8" bold="true" box="[185,249,906,932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FF4E08BC58A455F8" box="[185,244,906,932]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Note</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This name has been commonly listed as “ 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FD4C08BD5B1055F8" box="[699,832,906,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FD4C08BD5B1055F8" box="[699,832,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” although Dufour’s original name is 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FEE0089B59B8559B" authority="Linnæus, 1758" authorityName="Dufour" authorityYear="1831" box="[279,488,941,967]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Aranea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FEE0089B59B8559B" box="[279,488,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Aranea macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name was misspelled as “ 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FCCD08985B86559B" box="[826,982,941,967]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macululata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FCCD08985B86559B" box="[826,982,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macululata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FBFD089B595555B6" author="Simon E" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref20006" refString="Simon E (1885) Etudes sur les Arachnides recuellis en Tunisie en 1883 et 1884 par MM. A. Letourneux, M. Sedillot et Valery Mayet, membres de la mission de l'Exploration scientifique de la Tunisie. In: Exploration scientifique de la Tunisie. Paris, 1 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1885">Simon (1885: 28)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FEE708E6599B55B7" author="Karsch F" box="[272,459,976,1003]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref19013" refString="Karsch F (1881) Verzeichniss der wahrend der Rohlfs'schen Afrikanischen Expedition erbeuteten Myriopoden und Arachniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 47: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1881">Karsch (1881: 7)</bibRefCitation>
‘corrected’ the name to “ 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FD2808E65B1155B6" box="[735,833,976,1002]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FD2808E65B1155B6" box="[735,833,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” which was widely used. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5226DADFFB06739FF7B08C259245252" author="Bonnet P" box="[140,372,1011,1038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1926 - 3026" refId="ref18079" refString="Bonnet P (1957) Bibliographia Araneorum. Toulouse, Doladure 2 (3): 1926 - 3026." type="journal article" year="1957">Bonnet (1957: 2180</bibRefCitation>
; footnote) suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="16B36BDFFFB06739FD6008C55B455251" authority="Linnæus, 1758" authorityName="Dufour" authorityYear="1831" box="[663,789,1011,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Aranea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis id="E3C7CC4EFFB06739FD6008C55B455251" box="[663,789,1011,1037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poor Latin, being derived from a non-existent word “macullula” (“a small spot”). The consistent usage for over 100 years still does not validate Karsch’s emendation (ICZN Article 32b-c). In fact, Dufour’s original description (1831: 360) shows that his intention was to document a pattern of very small spots; and “macullula” is acceptable as an invented Latin word, parallel to the existing terms “medullula” or “ampullula” (H.D. Cameron, pers. comm. 1995).
</paragraph>
